South African Wheat Prices Fall After Decline by U.S. Benchmark

-- B y   M k h u l u l i   M a n c o t y w a
-- 
2011-02-21T10:45:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-21/south-african-wheat-prices-fall-after-decline-by-u-s-benchmark.html
Wheat fell in  South Africa ,
extending last week’s slide, after prices dropped in the U.S.  Wheat for March delivery, the most-active contract on the
 South African Futures Exchange , declined 77 rand, or 2.3
percent, to close at 3,248 rand ($454) a metric ton in
Johannesburg.  Wheat for May delivery lost 3.1 percent on the Chicago
Board of Trade on Feb. 18 on speculation that  China ’s demand for
grain and oilseeds will ease after the country took steps to
curb inflation. Chicago trading is closed today for the
Presidents’ Day holiday.  White corn for July delivery declined 26 rand, or 1.6
percent, to 1,646 rand a ton. Meal made from the grain is South
Africa’s staple food.  Yellow corn for July delivery dropped 24 rand, or 1.4
percent, to 1,689 rand a ton. The grain is used mainly for  animal feed  in South Africa.  The gains or losses for the most active contracts of the
following crops today were as follows. All prices are in rand
and the crops are sold in tons:  To contact the reporter on this story:
